Description:
Cash Flow Plus Location
The Lifestyle:
First Class in South Yarra's award winning Society project. Meters from the ever vibrant Chapel Street. Safety, security and entertainment are the buzz words for the occupier of this property.
Only a short walk to Prahran Market, Hawksburn Station, Trams and the Jam Factory makes this apartment the complete package..
The Living:
Immaculately presented, this over-sized studio apartment provides plenty of space for comfortable and convenient living. Offering a spacious open plan living along with a modern kitchen. The kitchen includes stainless steel appliances, gas cook top, integrated dishwasher and ample cupboard space.
The Basics:
- City Views from full width Balcony
- Balcony/Patio/Terrace
- Formal Entry
- Central Bathroom with great storage
- Euro Laundry
- Stone benches to kitchen including excellent appointments
- Reverse Cycle Heating and Cooling
- Gas Enabled
- Dishwasher
- Building Manager/Concierge
- Basement Car Park plus storage
Bonus Features:
Exceptional amenities such as gymnasium, spa, business centre, roof top indoor/outdoor entertaining.
What to do:
A fantastic opportunity awaits the astute investor equally for the first home buyer wanting to have it all at your doorstep! Call us to book a private inspection at 03 9820 0244 as this wont last long.

Description:
The Jewel of South Yarra
Located in the heart of South Yarra on Chapel Street, the Vogue Apartment stands out amongst others and it definitely has an array of pleasant surprises for residents. This stylish 2 bedrooms 1 bathrooms unit is located on the 15th floor with beautiful views all round. Building has great amenities such as heated indoor pool, Jacuzzi, sauna & steam rooms, tennis court and BBQ area.
Woolworths and Big W are situated just below the apartment building and Chapel St trams just a few steps away. A stones throw from South Yarra Train Station. This apartment has easy access to public transport.
Comprises:
- 2 bedrooms with Built in robes, master with ensuite
- Central bathroom
- Heating/cooling,
- Stylish kitchen with gas cooking
- European laundry

Description:
Idyllic Style and Lifestyle
Defined by timeless design, contemporary elegance and light-filled ambience, this refined executive residence is perfectly positioned within walking distance to every South Yarra attraction including Toorak Road shops, restaurants, cinemas and trams, Prahran Market, South Yarra station, Fawkner Park and schools.
An impressively proportioned formal sitting and dining room with gas fireplace and a light-filled and spacious casual living room are both served by a gourmet kitchen boasting timber and stone benches. The living area opens through bi-fold doors to a glorious private leafy north courtyard, ideal for al fresco dining. Sky-lit stairs lead up to the generous main bedroom with stylish en-suite, built in robe and views to Eureka Tower, a second double bedroom with built in robe, third bedroom or study and a bright bathroom. An oversized basement garage for 2 cars includes a large store-room or wine cellar.
Impeccably appointed with plantation shutters, alarm, powder-room, Euro-laundry and ample storage.

Description:
Light, Bright and an Absolute Delight
A spacious, unusually private two bedroom apartment in mint condition in this highly sought after security building amongst all the action in Chapel Street, next door to the Vogue Centre with Woolworths, Big W and lots of shops. The Como Centre is just up the road and the Yarra River close at hand. Public transport everywhere, South Yarra station close by or walk to the city.
Excellent kitchen with Smeg appliances, a large living area opening to a big balcony with bigger views.
Two bedrooms, family bathroom with big shower and Euro laundry. Undercover basement security parking and visitor parking. Large swimming pool, excellent gym and beautifully landscaped piazza gardens.
Building manager on site, ducted heating and cooling, NBN FTTP available for fast speed internet.
Currently leased with high quality furnishings to a quality tenant at $790 per week until January 2019. Furniture is optional and can be included upon request. A proven investment or an exciting place to live.

Description:
Urban Sanctuary in Prime Inner City Position
Designed for luxury living and entertaining, with multiple alfresco dining and relaxation areas, this spectacular townhouse is grand in scale and offers sublime dual level living. Privately positioned behind a secure high fence with intercom entrance, the north facing front courtyard precedes bi-fold doors opening to a casual sitting room with a tranquil outlook over the front patio. A central chef’s kitchen with five burner gas SMEG cooktop and oven, ASKO dishwasher, granite benchtops and breakfast bar adjoins a dining area and laidback family room which flows to the private rear courtyard with pergola and direct access to the lock up garage. A well designed powder room and under-stair storage ensure no space is wasted. Upstairs the sophisticated master suite includes multiple wardrobes, built-in cabinetry, north facing balcony and a magnificent ensuite, two further south facing bedrooms offering built in storage, a versatile study potentially doubling as an additional living/TV zone, a sumptuous bathroom with separate bath and shower and a walk-through laundry with abundant storage. Every lifestyle factor has been taken into account here with heating and cooling throughout, clever and copious storage options and an emphasis on maximising natural light. The position just moments from Toorak Road and Chapel Street, South Yarra Station, Fawkner Park and Prahran Market is sure to entice.

Description:
Spectacular Scale, Premium Style
A brilliant design to capitalise on the north/south aspect, expertly executed to maximise space and light in a convenient locale, cement this dual level town residence as one of premium quality and low maintenance, ideal for the family home buyer, downsizer or investor. The initial expectations created by the stately facade do not disappoint as the spectacular interior offers contemporary spaces designed with distinction. Living/dining areas of stunning scale and style are surrounded by full height windows and include an impressive open plan kitchen with breakfast bar and dishwasher. A paved rear courtyard garden is supremely private with high walls and two cars are easily accommodated with off street parking in the driveway plus a lock up garage with internal access. A north facing master suite with walk in robe and ensuite enjoys its own private balcony, two further bedrooms with built in robes share a rear balcony with a private outlook all well serviced by the central bathroom with shower over bath and a European laundry. Multiple split system heating/cooling units, fresh paint, new carpet and high ceilings add to the value. Prahran Station and Market, trams, cafes, supermarkets and boutique shops are all on the doorstep.

Description:
Picturesque Edwardian, perfect location
Combining contemporary style with timeless elegance, this renovated Edwardian residence, in the tightly held Hawksburn precinct, showcases generous spaces awash with brilliant natural light. Timber floors create a natural flow through the welcoming hallway, leading to two bedrooms with built in robes. Spacious living and dining opens through bi fold glass doors to the rear courtyard, landscaped gardens and alfresco dining area, offering the perfect indoor-outdoor lifestyle, while a superb kitchen boasts quality stainless steel appliances set against stylish feature mirror tiles and stone benchtops. Includes a skylit bathroom and laundry plus excellent storage including roof storage, heating and cooling and study nook. Enjoying an ultra convenient location close to Hawksburn and Toorak Villages, Como Park and Hawksburn Station.

Description:
Light, Space and Views!
Desirably situated in a premier leafy South Yarra street, just a shady walk to all the attractions of Toorak Road and Chapel Street, this bright and spacious, stylishly renovated two bedroom apartment enjoys a wonderful treetop and city skyline outlook. This top floor retreat is superbly presented and gives buyers a cosmopolitan taste of the South Yarra good life. The generous, central lounge is filled with natural light and is an ideal space to relax day and night. Just off the lounge, the kitchen and meals area has been freshly renovated and comprises abundant storage along with stainless steel DeLonghi/Westinghouse appliances. Both bedrooms have built-in robes including the sizeable main bedroom, a fully renovated bathroom with a separate toilet. Features include reverse cycle air conditioning, additional heating, secure intercom entry and an undercover car space. Kensington Road is in one of the suburb's best locations close to cafes, restaurants, and shops on Toorak Road and Chapel Street, Como Park, Yarra River bike/walking tracks, Vogue Shopping Plaza, Toorak Village, Como Centre with Palace Cinema, trams, and Hawksburn Station.

Description:
Boutique Inner-City Living with Oversized Appeal
Location perfection with the best of Melbourne at your fingertips, this second-floor corner apartment sets itself apart from all others with its impressively spacious interior, quality enhancements and leafy outlook from every window. Secluded, serene and bathed in natural light, the home's immaculately-presented interior comprises two genuinely large bedrooms (both with built-in robes), stylish central bathroom and separate powder room. Add to this an expansive open-design living/dining area leading out to an undercover balcony complete with city skyline views. Other stand-out features include a contemporary kitchen with soft-close drawers, stainless steel cooking appliances and integrated Smeg dishwasher, as well as split-system heating/cooling, internal laundry facilities, intercom, plus secure entry foyer and undercover off-street parking space. Royal Botanic Gardens at one end of the street and Fawkner Park the other, it's also walking distance to a choice of tram lines, Melbourne Grammar School and Mac Robertson Girls High School, easy access to Toorak Road/Chapel Street shops and eateries, as well as the Alfred Hospital, Citylink and the open spaces of Albert Park. First time offered in nearly 40 years - what an opportunity!

Description:
"Ilfracombe" - c1880
A landmark c1880s Victorian residence with an illustrious provenance and magnificent original elegance and grandeur, "Ilfracombe" is exclusively situated in a prized South Yarra Hill location just moments from Toorak Road's boutiques and restaurants, the Botanic Gardens and elite schools.
Behind a high walled lush garden, a chequerboard marble entrance foyer introduces a refined library, gracious sitting room with alcove and elegant formal dining room all featuring high ornate ceilings, marble fireplaces and exquisite leadlight windows. The inviting family living room with a marble gas fire and casual dining room with an original iron stove surround a spacious gourmet kitchen appointed with granite benches and a butler's pantry. A sensational conservatory provides idyllic year round indoor-outdoor dining and entertaining overlooking the landscaped northeast garden featuring extensive paving and a heated swim-jet pool and spa. An imposing mahogany staircase leads up to the beautiful main bedroom with marble fireplace, walk in robe and en-suite, three additional double bedrooms with marble fireplaces, 5th bedroom and a marble bathroom. A versatile large retreat or 6th bedroom on the level above opens to a balcony offering views to the Dandenongs. Adjacent to the internally accessed 5-car garage there is an atmospheric bluestone and exposed brick basement comprising a billiards room, wine cellar and bar-room.
"Ilfracombe" also includes an alarm, security intercom, hydronic heating, powder-room, laundry, irrigation and auto gates. Land size: 660sqm approx.
Inspect by appointment at the advertised times.

Description:
Basking in Sun, Impeccable North Facing Apartment
Warm and spacious with an abundance of natural light, this charming top floor apartment entices with generous proportions and endless character. Impeccably maintained with timeless appeal, the north facing apartment offers a tranquil leafy outlook from each window. A substantial floorplan comprises of a sun filled L-shaped lounge and dining area with balcony, an immaculate kitchen with gas cooktop and dishwasher, large bedroom with panel heating and built in robes plus a sizeable bathroom with shower over bath. Secure off street parking, excellent internal storage, timber floorboards, intercom entrance, reverse cycle heating/cooling and Rinnai heater are included. Occupying a peaceful position well back from Toorak Road towards the rear of the complex, the home is ideally located only moments to Chapel Street and Rockley Gardens with quick access to the CBD via the tram on your front doorstep or South Yarra train station.

Description:
UNDER OFFER Beautiful Corner Apartment at The Claremont
The Building
Designed by Bird de la Coeur Architects, the building represent modern luxury at its finest. The moment you arrive and walk past the large glass entrance doors, you will come upon a spiral marble-sculpture like stairwell that leads to an expansive space where the lifts are located. A large glassed off library sits at the bottom left of the stairwell with views of the front street. This library/lounge area provides its residents and their guests a beautiful cosy occlusive space to hang out and relax.
The amenities are located on the 5th floor and it features a beautifully designed winter lounge, an outdoor deck, pool and gym.
The Apartment
Classically designed with practicality in mind; all living areas have floor to ceiling windows which maximises the amount of natural lighting that comes into the apartment. The kitchen is fitted out with European appliances that includes a Bosch refrigerator, and a movable island bench that is perfect for apartment living. The bedroom has a large doorway which gives off a hint of grandeur.
The Attraction
Superbly located in central South Yarra; walking distance to the famous Toorak Road and Chapel Street where the finest shopping, restaurants, cafes and bars can be found.
Tram stops and the South Yarra Train station are within extreme close vicinity.

Description:
Exquisite Elegance and Luxury
Delivering an incomparable inner urban lifestyle, this captivating residence's versatile floorplan effortlessly caters to modern family requirements with a sophisticated sense of style. Behind a stunning contemporary façade, American Oak floors, soaring ceilings, extensive glass and walnut accents define the interior spaces. Generously proportioned open plan living with bespoke cabinetry flows through full height and width glass sliding doors to a private north facing deck with custom in built seating, providing the perfect space for relaxing and entertaining. The dining area incorporates a state of the art kitchen boasting marble benchtops and splashback, walk in pantry and a suite of high end appliances including integrated Asko dishwasher, Miele oven and gas cook top. A stylish main bedroom with lavish bluestone appointed ensuite and walk in robe is accompanied by a second bedroom with walk in robe, third bedroom with built in robes and an elegant family bathroom fitted with freestanding bath. Additionally includes separate laundry, study with built in desk, cleverly designed storage, video intercom, heating, cooling, solar hot water and parking. Ideally positioned walking distance to every South Yarra amenity including Fawkner Park, shopping and dining on Toorak Road and Chapel Street, Prahran Market, South Yarra Station, trams and South Yarra Primary School.

Description:
Quality Designer Living, Unbeatable Location
Your passport to a vibrant Chapel St lifestyle, this captivating, architectural designed "Neometro" apartment combines extraordinarily large dimensions with a hint of contemporary industrial styling. Unusually large for such a modern apartment, this bright and sophisticated home is a compelling option for down-sizing empty-nesters, investors and owner-occupiers seeking a lifestyle edge.
As it eases effortlessly through huge floor-to-ceiling sliding glass doors to a sunny, full-width balcony, the open-plan living is impressively proportioned and stylishly appointed with SMEG kitchen appliances, an integrated refrigerator, alcove study nook and marble benches. Secure parking, intercom entry, elevator access are particularly appealing attributes in this home with reverse cycle air conditioning, robes and attractive timber floors.
The lifestyle appeal of this blue ribbon location is without peer, just metres from one of Melbourne's most popular strips of cafes, restaurants, bars and shops, as well as cinemas at the Jam Factory and all modes of public transport.

An address that for generations was associated with enjoying life's celebrations and landmark occasions, the new 'Nine Darling' delivers a residential experience that's defined by excellence. Description:
Affordable blue chip Botanic Gardens apartment
An affordable Blue-Chip investment, first home or city pad in one of South Yarra’s best streets, with the Royal Botanic Gardens at one end and Fawkner Park at the other. Offering a separate study for those that like to work from home or a little extra space.
Offering secure one bedroom plus study accommodation, open plan living / dining / kitchen with gas cooking, main bedroom with BIRs, and separate study on title. Presenting the benefits of inner city living, flexibility of working from home, this apartment will not be available for long. All within a boutique block of only 15 apartments with low owners corporation fees.
Who wants to live or own a fabulous entry level, blue chip apartment in the centre of the universe? Offering Entrecote (a French restaurant and renowned coffee window at the rear) across the street and Domain Road shops and cafes around the corner. All within striking distance of St Kilda Road, the city CBD, MCG, AAMI Park, Melbourne Park tennis centre (Rod Laver and Margaret Court Arenas), renowned “Tan” track, Shrine of Remembrance, the Kings Domain, Yarra River, Albert Park Lake and access to major arterials (Monash Freeway and Westgate Bridge) at your doorstep.
Two residential parking permits are available for this apartment from Melbourne City Council for your peace of mind.
Be quick as this one will not last!
**SOHO= Small office, Home office
